21 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Prohibition on foreign national interference in statewide ballot
22 issues. (1) A foreign national may not, directly or indirectly through any person or entity, do the following:
23 (a) make a contribution, expenditure, or independent expenditure in support of or in opposition to a
24 statewide ballot issue, regardless of whether the ballot issue has been certified to appear on the ballot;
25 (b) make a disbursement for the direct cost of producing or airing an ELECTION COMMUNICATION OR
26 AN electioneering communication; or
